Package com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql

Interface Table

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<Table>
All Known Implementing Classes:
SQLTable
public interface Table extends Comparable<Table>
Represents a Database Table.
A table generates columns based on Class Fields. This library will take fields from parent classes as well.
It is highly recommended to have a primary key field as the library allows you to update existing data for a specific object.
You can have fields ignored using one of the following ways: The Ignored annotation, the modifiers; static AND final, transient
Fields that are sub-classes of Collection and Map must be used with the Codec annotation for custom processing, or using the ForeignKey system. Fields that have types extended from ObservableValue will be ignored unless annotated with Codec with an appropriate codec You must have a field that is an ID column for it to work. You can technically use any object as it though. The two ways you can do it is from the ID annotation or using the PrimaryKey annotation.
The ID annotation will automatically set it as the Primary Key and as an AutoIncrement if it an object type that this library supports as such.
Note: Fields that are of type long, Long, int or Integer and named id are automatically set as the ID field. This is for compatibility with existing projects that I have.
